This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with clustering in Wireless Sensor Networks, which is a networking topic. It could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as clustering is a technique for organizing data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper addresses the issue of reliability of communication links, which is a security concern. It could also be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper proposes a protocol for controlling the behavior of the network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper incorporates a composite metric that includes different notions of link reliability, which is a concept from information theory.
